# PortMaster-New sync

When syncing `jkdf2/port/` to `~/PortMaster-New/ports/openjkdf2/`, use `scripts/sync-portmaster-new.sh`.

**Do not copy** `libs.aarch64/.gitkeep`, `libs.x86_64/.gitkeep`, or any `libs.*/.gitkeep` into PortMaster-New. Those placeholders exist only in the dev repo to keep empty `libs.*` dirs in git; the PortMaster port ships real `.so` files instead.

Also exclude dev/runtime junk: `log.txt`, `jk1/registry.json`, `jk1/openjkdf2_cvars.json`, `conf/mp.conf`.

Helper scripts inside `openjkdf2/` use **`.run`** (not `.sh`) so EmulationStation does not list them as ports — e.g. `run-dedicated.run`. Docker-only helpers live under `helpers/` (e.g. `helpers/mpserver-entrypoint.run`). Game launchers stay as `*.sh` at `ports/openjkdf2/`.

After rsync, remove any stale `libs.*/.gitkeep`, `run-mpserver.run`, or root-level `mpserver-entrypoint.sh` left in the PortMaster-New tree before committing.
